        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the negative battery terminal.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install switch part number 2041792C91 to bracket 3516159C1 with screws 28199R1 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9708021" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9708021.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the switch and bracket assembly to the pedal assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install bracket part number 3516160C1 to the pedal assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the pedal operates normally and floormats do not interfere with switch operation.
                    Trim off excess switch toggle arm material as needed to eliminate interference (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and cut circuit wire 92E in the wire harness near the modulator solenoid relay (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708022">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9708022" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9708022.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use 16 ga. wire and butt splice connectors 2027570C1 to extend circuit 92E to switch
                    2041792C91 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708022">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach insulated blade connectors 592952C1 to the wire extensions and install to the
                    outer terminals on switch 2041792C91(
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9708023">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9708023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9708023.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There are three terminals on switch 2041792C91. Do not use the center terminal (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9708023">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the negative battery terminal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With key On and engine Off, monitor percent accelerator using a ProLink and adjust the
                    bracket on the pedal assembly for modulator On at 70% throttle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Road test the vehicle and monitor modulator operation. 12 volts should be present at the
                    modulator at 70% throttle.
                </para>
            </step1>
